I"Û<p><strong>Windows SAPI</strong> is a nice tool that comes with Windows that allows us to transform an input <strong>text into a speech</strong>.</p>

<p>Ok, this is quite simpleâ€¦takes only 3 lines of code, so not much explanation is needed.</p>

<h2 id="how-to">How to?</h2>

<p>Right click on the projectâ€™s name (in Solution Explorer)-&gt;<strong>Add Reference</strong>-&gt;<strong>COM</strong> and look for <strong>Microsoft Speech Object Library</strong>, select it then click Ok.</p>

<p>Now include the following line, near the first lines of code (where the namespaces are included):</p>

